Are the Priorihominus also intended to be the creators of SCP-1795?
附加记录：    

It wasn't my intention, but I was aware of SCP-1795 when putting together some of the ideas here. I will say that the two have undeniable thematic similarities and both involve an advanced early human presence.

To add to this, even a basic analysis of the Priorihominus civilization points to them having a wide interstellar reach, with sufficiently advanced (para-)technology.1 Large-scale planetary manufacturing might look a bit outside their capabilities  but we also don't have a timescale! If these are generation ships, then it's likely they were launched in the infancy of their extrasolar civilization.

+territory

–block


Couple things:

The  is pattern screamers, which can be linked to their appearance in 1795. Additionally, the debris field is similar to what post-3426 would look like (albeit on the extreme end of the spectrum).
Something that came before us did have the capacity to create megastructures beyond the planetary scale.





So, if you do want to headcanon a connection, I definitely won't protest it!

Footnotes
1. They had the industrial and engineering capacity to manufacture a fleet of Klein bottle generation ships, and were familiar with this  when they found it.









